This paper discusses a technique commonly used in machine learning (Gibbs sampling) and focuses on improving its efficiency through parallelization. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the challenges of Markov chain analysis, which is a topic related to Data Structures (cs.DS) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents experimental results, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Mathematics (cs.MA).
